[1] Cases in various countries
Asia
---
Pakistan
- Sindh (Karachi). 7 Feb 2018. At least 19 more cases of dengue fever were reported in Karachi in a week, taking the toll of reported cases in 2018 to 107. According to the weekly report issued by Prevention and Control Program for Dengue in Sindh, a total of 110 cases have been reported throughout Sindh so far out of which 107 were in Karachi and the other 3 in the rest of the province. No death has been reported due to dengue fever this month [February 2018] so far. In 2017, a total of 2927 cases of dengue fever were reported across Sindh out of which 12 lost their lives to the disease.
https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2018/02/07/another-19-dengue-fever-cases-reported-in-karachi/

Saudi Arabia
- Jeddah. 28 Jan 2018. Dengue fever cases in Jeddah dropped by 38 percent in 2017.The awareness campaign helped bring down the number of dengue cases in the city by 50.7 percent compared to the same period in the previous year [2017]. The health affairs directorate announced last March [2017] when it launched the awareness campaign that it had registered 500 cases during the previous 10 weeks.
http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/article/527068/SAUDI-ARABIA/Dengue-fever-cases-in-Jeddah-drop-by-38

Cambodia.
- National. 5 Feb 2018. A report from the ministry said that in the 1st 3 weeks of 2018, there was a 130 percent spike in cases when compared to the 1st 3 weeks of 2017. The report added that dengue fever outbreaks usually occur every 5 to 6 years.

The ministry said that in the 1st 3 weeks of 2018, there were 316 cases of dengue fever and one death, an increase of 130 percent when compared to the 138 cases and zero deaths for the same time period in 2017.

The warning that a spike could be coming in 2018 follows news that cases were cut in half in 2017 when compared to 2016. The number of dengue fever cases dropped by more than half in 2017, with only 3 deaths.

Huy Rekol, director of the National Centre for Parasitology, Entomology and Malaria Control, said there were 6372 cases of dengue fever in the country in 2017. In 2016, there were 12 843 cases, with 18 deaths.
http://www.khmertimeskh.com/50106515/health-ministry-issues-dengue-fever-warning/

Pacific
---
- Tonga. 30 Jan 2018. Tonga has declared a dengue outbreak following the death of a New Zealand girl in the country last week. The 12-year-old had been visiting family in Tonga over the Christmas holidays. The chief executive of Tonga's Ministry of Health said there were 19 confirmed cases of dengue in the country, all on the main island Tonga'tapu.
https://www.radionz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/349271/dengue-death-and-outbreak-confirmed-in-tonga

- Tonga. 1 Feb 2018. A national campaign to control the spread of dengue started today as the number of people who have caught the disease climbed to 33 as of this afternoon, 1 February. Schools are waiting for funding to start spraying.
http://matangitonga.to/2018/02/01/dengue-cases-climb-33

- Tonga. 5 Feb 2018. As dengue cases increase to 52 on Tongatapu as of this afternoon, 5 February, a medical officer from the Ministry of Health admitted they lack the ability to treat hemorrhagic dengue because they are waiting to replace a broken centrifuge.
http://matangitonga.to/2018/02/05/tonga-lacks-equipment-treat-hemorrhagic-dengue

