[2] Vaccination
Date: Sun 4 Feb 2018 3:10pm
Source: Gizmodo [edited]
https://gizmodo.com/the-philippines-halts-mass-use-of-dengue-fever-vaccine-1822695721


On [Fri 2 Feb 2018], Filipino authorities tied at least 3 deaths to the 2016
deployment of Dengvaxia, the world's 1st dengue fever vaccine, Reuters
reported.

Vaccine manufacturer Sanofi Pasteur admitted in November [2017] that the vaccine, Dengvaxia, might increase the odds of severe illness in inoculated children who had not previously been infected with the dengue virus. Over 800 000 children were injected with the vaccine, and a panel of experts formed to investigate 14 deaths concluded that at least 3 had "causal
association," per Reuters:

"Up to 3 cases were found to have causal association. They died of dengue even (though) they were given Dengvaxia. Two of them may have died because of vaccine failure," Health Undersecretary Enrique Domingo told a news conference.

"These findings strengthen the decision of the Department of Health to stop
the vaccine. It has failed in some children. Dengvaxia is not ready for mass
vaccinations and we would need 3 to 5 more years to watch and monitor
if there would be other adverse reactions from the vaccine."

[By: Tom McKay]

